@database main "MAXTetris"
@node main "MAXTetris by R. Smith"

MAXTetris is a Tetris style game door for MAXs BBS.

@{"Installation" link inst}
@{"The Game" link game}
@{"Contact" link cont}
@{"History" link hist}
@{"Copyright" link copy}
@{"Thanks" link greet}
@endnode
@node inst "Installing MAXTetris"
Installation is simple. You must also assign @{B}Doors:@{UB} somewhere
(probably already done).
Copy all the ANSI files and the 680x0 executable to @{B}doors:tetris@{UB}.
An assign may be necessary.

The function of the ANSI files should be fairly obvious.

The game will create a high scores file called tetris.score in its 
directory.
@endnode
@node game "Playing the game"
The keys for the game are as follows:

	z: Rotate left
	x: Rotate right
	4: Move left
	5: Move down (faster)
	6: Move right
@endnode
